          "key": "C",
          "text": "8 bits"
        },
        {
          "key": "D",
          "text": "26 bits"
        }
      ],
      "correctAnswer": "2 bits",
      "explanation": "Default Class C is /24. /26 means 2 additional bits are borrowed (24 to 26).",
      "difficulty": "hard"
    },
    {
      "id": "mcq-14",
      "question": "Which subnet mask provides exactly 128 subnets from a Class C?",
      "options": [
        {
          "key": "A",
          "text": "255.255.255.0"
        },
        {
          "key": "B",
          "text": "255.255.255.128"
        },
        {
          "key": "C",
          "text": "255.255.255.192"
        },
        {
          "key": "D",
          "text": "255.255.255.224"
        }
      ],
      "correctAnswer": "255.255.255.192",
      "explanation": "255.255.255.192 is /26. From /24, borrowing 2 bits creates 2^2 = 4 subnets. To get 128, need 7 bits: 2^7 = 128, so /24+7=/31.",
      "difficulty": "hard"
    },
